stories.title: Smith and Hall banned, Youhana fined in Code of Conduct hearing
stories.summary: South Africa captain Graeme Smith has been banned for one One-Day International (ODI) and fined 50% of his match fee, team-mate Andrew Hall has been banned for one ODI and two Test Matches and Pakistan's Yousuf Youhana has been fined 50% of his match

stories.title: Smith, Hall and Youhana charged by ICC
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v South Africa ODI series
stories.summary: Andrew Hall and Yousuf Youhana have been hauled before an ICC Code of Conduct meeting after their mid-pitch confrontation in the second ODI at Lahore last Sunday, following a review of video footage of the incident

stories.title: Smith, Hall and Youhana face ICC Code of Conduct charges
stories.summary: South Africa captain Graeme Smith, all-rounder Andrew Hall and Pakistan batsmen Yousuf Youhana will face ICC Match Referee Clive Lloyd after the International Cricket Council charged all three players following a review of footage taken from the

stories.title: ICC to review footage of incident from second ODI in Pakistan
stories.summary: The ICC said today that it would wait until after it had received a full report and reviewed the available footage of an incident involving South Africa's Andrew Hall and Pakistan batsmen Yousuf Youhana before deciding if any charges should be laid

stories.title: ICC to investigate Hall-Youhana incident
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v South Africa, 2nd ODI
stories.summary: The standoff between Andrew Hall and Yousuf Youhana in the second ODI at Lahore on Sunday is under scrutiny

stories.title: Yousuf Youhana takes Pakistan to 2-0 lead
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v South Africa, 2nd ODI, Lahore
stories.summary: Chasing under lights yet again in the second game of their one-day series against Pakistan, South Africa could not resist the pressure for long enough to make a realistic assault on their target of 268, falling short by 42 runs
